OverHistory.UPDCommentry: Tim Southee gets Rohit Sharma for the 5th time in T20 cricket! WICKET Rohit Sharma c Sheldon Jackson b Tim Southee (Mumbai Indians 2 Runs for 1 wicket), Tim Southee bowling to Rohit Sharma, short of good length ball, pitching outside off stump, nips back in slightly and hits Rohit Sharma on his though on the way to the keeper, there is an appeal for the caught behind and Shreyas Iyer takes this upstairs after the umpire signals Not-Out, UltraEdge shows a spike as ball passes the bat and the onfield decision is overturned. Rohit looks dejected as there were murmurs even before the ball had passed the bat but he has to depart.
